                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d611">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Bowers, Claude G/75: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Straus</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="64" xml:id="d611fn64">Sent to U. S. S. <hi rend="italic"
                            >Oklahoma</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Cayuga</hi> for their
                        information.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-07-26T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 26, 1936—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>256. Your 660, July 26, 9 p.m I have talked with Schoelkopf<note n="65"
                        xml:id="d611fn65">Walter H. Schoelkopf, First Secretary of Embassy in
                        Spain.</note> at St. Jean de Luz, this evening and told him that Ambassador
                    Bowers has my authorization to leave Fuenterrabia for France or elsewhere and
                    should not remain on endangering himself and family.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
